Paper: hep-th/0111132

Date: 2001-11-14

Title: Localization of Fields on a Brane in Six Dimensions

Authors: Merab Gogberashvili and Paul Midodashvili

Comments: 6 pages, LaTeX, no figures, two references added, minor changes.

Version to appear in Europhysics LettersJournal-ref: Europhys.Lett. 61 (2003) 308-313

Universe is considered as a brane in infinite (2+4)-space.It is shown thatzero modes of all kinds of matter fields and 4-gravity are localized on thebrane by increasing transversal gravitational potential.